\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Double exchange of particles is topologically equivalent to one particle winding around the other. \textbf  {(a)} Double exchange process of two particles. \textbf  {(b)} Inner loop can be deformed in a continuous manner until it is infinitesimally small. \textbf  {(c)} When the inner loop has been deformed to be of 0 size, the outer particle simply winds around the inner particle.}}{12}{figure.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:doubleswap}{{6}{12}{Double exchange of particles is topologically equivalent to one particle winding around the other. \textbf {(a)} Double exchange process of two particles. \textbf {(b)} Inner loop can be deformed in a continuous manner until it is infinitesimally small. \textbf {(c)} When the inner loop has been deformed to be of 0 size, the outer particle simply winds around the inner particle}{figure.6}{}}
